        "title": "fix: theme header search tabs",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fix the header search typeahead tabs so light mode uses light segmented-control colors.\n- Keep the previous dark segmented colors behind an explicit dark-theme override.\n- Add a regression assertion for theme-aware typeahead tab CSS.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `bun run test -- src/__tests__/header.test.tsx`\n- `bun run format:check -- src/styles.css src/__tests__/header.test.tsx`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `bun run lint`\n- `bun run deadcode:ci`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n- `bun run ci:static` fails at `bun audit` before lint/deadcode because current dependency advisories are not ignored: `dompurify` GHSA-cmwh-pvxp-8882 and `undici` GHSA-vmh5-mc38-953g / GHSA-pr7r-676h-xcf6.\n\n## Screenshot\n\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vyctorbrzezowski/clawhub/qa-artifacts/clawhub-ui-proof/pr-2737/header-search-tabs-light-local/candidate/01-header-search-tabs-light-theme.png\" width=\"420\" alt=\"Header search tabs in light theme\">\n\nRaw proof files: https://github.com/vyctorbrzezowski/clawhub/tree/qa-artifacts/clawhub-ui-proof/pr-2737/header-search-tabs-light-local\n",
